Dockerfile example:
FROM ubuntu:latest

ADD https://raw.githubusercontent.com/konstruktoid/Docker/master/Security/cleanBits.sh /tmp/cleanBits.sh

RUN \
        apt-get update && \
        apt-get -y upgrade && \
        apt-get -y clean && \ 
		apt-get -y autoremove

RUN \
		adduser --system --no-create-home --group --disabled-password --shell /bin/false dockeru
        /bin/bash /tmp/cleanBits.sh

CMD ["bash"]

Docker run options:
Time:
-v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro

Log:
-v /dev/log:/dev/log

Capabilities:
~$ docker run --rm --name name -t image
~$ docker exec `docker ps -q` ps a | awk '{print $1}' | grep -v PID
~$ docker exec `docker ps -q` cat /proc/1/status | grep CapEff | awk '{print $NF}'
~$ docker exec `docker ps -q` capsh --decode=00000020a80425fb | sed -e 's/.*=//' -e 's/cap_/--cap-add /g' -e 's/,/ /g'
~$ curl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/torvalds/linux/master/include/uapi/linux/capability.h | grep " CAP_" | awk '{print $2, $3}'

~$ export CAP="--cap-drop all --cap-add dac_override --cap-add fowner --cap-add fsetid --cap-add kill --cap-add setpcap --cap-add net_bind_service --cap-add net_raw --cap-add audit_write --cap-add setfcap"
~$ docker run --rm -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro -v /dev/log:/dev/log $CAP --name $@ -t <IMAGE>
~$ docker run --rm -u dockeru -v /etc/localtime:/etc/localtime:ro -v /dev/log:/dev/log $CAP --name $@ -t <IMAGE>

Docker daemon options:
--icc=false

Docker daemon host:
Lock it down with a firewall, remove SUID/GUID, password policies, stricter SSH configuration, ...
http://konstruktoid.net/2014/07/07/ubuntu_config-sh-stricter-settings-for-your-ubuntu-server/